310 Gladstone Crescent is located just south of Marquis Drive and the future north commuter bridge scheduled for completion in 2018. This build to suit opportunity is expected to appeal to a variety of  industrial, showcase, retail, and office users. This property has excellent exposure backing Wanuskewin Road.

Common.SubdivisionName.Common.UnitDisplayName: Grasswood Junction – English River Office Building

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: English River at Grasswood Junction is a 135-acre property located just two kilometres south of Circle Drive on the northwest corner of Highway 11 and Grasswood Road, one of Saskatoon’s busiest regional crossroads. Grasswood Junction considers all the needs of a successful business park with both light industrial and warehouse space, plans for a second office building with room to grow and provisions for surrounding amenities including mixed retail and a hotel to serve the population of the park and the surrounding areas. The site master plan also includes ample parking, infrastructure and green space. Additionally, the planned English River Office building is engineered to draw office users that seek a decorative office environment. A high-performance building envelope and the energy efficient mechanical and electrical systems are an eco-friendly option and provide maximum occupant comfort.
